President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama send their warmest greetings to those celebrating Eid al-Fitr in the United States and around the world. They highlight the importance of Eid for Muslim Americans to reflect on the month of fasting and recommit to values of gratitude, compassion, and generosity. The President emphasizes the diversity of Muslim Americans and their contributions to the nation's history and strength. He also acknowledges the challenges and violence experienced during Ramadan, expressing condolences for those affected. The President condemns attacks against Muslim Americans and reaffirms the importance of protecting them against bigotry and xenophobia. The Obamas will host an Eid celebration at the White House later in the month. The statement concludes with Eid Mubarak greetings from their family.